description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated Band 6 Community therapist (Occupational Therapist or Physiotherapist) to join the North East Community Therapy service based at Bicester Community Hospital, Oxfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service currently consists of dedicated and skilled staff providing community based therapy across the North East of Oxfordshire with the aim of improving quality of life for service users, avoid unnecessary hospital admissions and support timely discharges home from the acute sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professional support offered by Oxford Health NHS Foundation Trust:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A comprehensive Induction programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A structured In Service Training programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding supervision and Personal Development support and programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A robust career development scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Therapy is at the forefront of current government initiatives to deliver more healthcare out of acute hospitals and closer to home with the aim of providing better care for patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will offer you the opportunity to work as a part of a multi-disciplinary Neighbourhood team consisting of Occupational therapists, Physiotherapists, District Nurses, GP’s, Mental Health Practitioners, Social Services partners as well as Acute Trust partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop your skills as a specialist Physiotherapist/Occupational Therapist within a community setting. This includes completing complex community assessment- and treatment interventions alongside additional generic skills to provide a comprehensive assessment to a variety of complex patients as part of the Aging Well national agenda and the Frailty pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own car or access to alternative travel for business use is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tanya du Preez&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: tanya.du-preez@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07917534253&lt;/p&gt;
